sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as data-science-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant MLflow as MLflow Server<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS (service-ca)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant DB as PostgreSQL/MySQL<br/>5432/TCP or 3306/TCP
    participant S3 as S3 Storage<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(230, 245, 255)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 1: MLflow API Request via Gateway
        Client->>Gateway: POST /mlflow/api/2.0/...<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
        Gateway->>MLflow: Forward request<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Forwarded Bearer Token
        MLflow->>K8sAPI: SelfSubjectAccessReview<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        K8sAPI-->>MLflow: AuthZ decision (allow/deny)
        MLflow->>DB: Query/Store metadata<br/>TCP/5432, TLS verify-full<br/>Auth: Connection string
        DB-->>MLflow: Query results
        MLflow->>S3: Store/Retrieve artifacts<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS<br/>Auth: AWS credentials (env)
        S3-->>MLflow: Artifact data
        MLflow-->>Gateway: JSON Response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 245, 230)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 2: Database Migration (Version Upgrade)
        participant Operator as MLflow Operator
        participant MigJob as Migration Job Pod

        Operator->>K8sAPI: Watch MLflow CR change<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Scale Deployment to 0<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS
        Note over Operator: Wait for pods to drain
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Migration Job<br/>(reuses Deployment pod spec)
        K8sAPI-->>MigJob: Job pod scheduled
        MigJob->>DB: mlflow db upgrade<br/>TCP/5432, TLS<br/>Auth: Connection string
        DB-->>MigJob: Migration complete
        MigJob-->>Operator: Job succeeded (exit 0)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Restore Deployment replicas<br/>HTTPS/6443, TLS
    end

    rect rgb(245, 255, 230)
        Note over Client,S3: Flow 3: Garbage Collection
        participant GCJob as GC CronJob Pod

        Note over GCJob: Scheduled CronJob fires
        GCJob->>DB: Delete soft-deleted metadata<br/>TCP/5432, TLS<br/>Auth: Connection string
        DB-->>GCJob: Rows deleted
        GCJob->>MLflow: Delete artifacts (proxied)<br/>HTTPS/8443, TLS (service-ca)<br/>Auth: Kubernetes auth (SA token)
        MLflow->>S3: Delete artifact files<br/>HTTPS/443, TLS
        S3-->>MLflow: Deleted
        MLflow-->>GCJob: Artifact deletion confirmed
    end
